  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="section faq-section" id="faq" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about ecommerce AI search optimisation in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Ecommerce AI Search Optimisation Questions Answered</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>Why do ecommerce stores need AI search optimisation?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Shoppers increasingly ask AI platforms like ChatGPT and Gemini for product and store recommendations before making purchases. If your online store isn't in those AI answers, you're losing high-intent buyers to competitors that AI does recommend. AI-referred traffic converts at 4.4x the rate of traditional search traffic.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>How is ecommerce GEO different from regular ecommerce SEO?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Ecommerce SEO focuses on ranking product pages in Google search results. Ecommerce GEO ensures AI platforms recommend your store when shoppers ask questions like "best online store for sneakers in Singapore". The overlap between Google rankings and AI citations is below 20%, so strong Google rankings alone won't get you into AI recommendations.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
          <summary>Which AI platforms matter most for ecommerce?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>ChatGPT, Google Gemini, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and Microsoft Copilot all influence purchasing decisions. Google AI Overviews appears directly in search results, while ChatGPT and Perplexity are increasingly used for product research and comparison shopping. We optimise for all five platforms.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How long before my online store appears in AI recommendations?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Most ecommerce businesses see measurable improvements in AI citation rates within 30 to 90 days. Product schema implementation and structured data fixes can produce quick wins within weeks. Building product authority and review signals compounds over time for sustained visibility.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>How much does ecommerce AI search optimisation cost in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Our GEO plans start at $3,000 SGD/month for the Essentials package covering AI audits, product schema markup, and content optimisation. Growth plans at $5,000/month add authority building and a dedicated strategist. Enterprise plans from $10,000/month provide full-service AI search domination for large catalogues.</p></div>
        </details>
